4. Pantheon DSL (Ω-Surface Layer) — v0.1

Purpose

A lightweight symbolic interface for interacting with the Pantheon system
(Ω-Lang influence, but NOT meaning-locked)

⸻

Example Syntax

NODE Decision_01 {
  INPUT: "Invest $1000 this week"
  
  CONSTRAINTS: [
    ethics >= 0.7,
    reversibility == true,
    risk <= medium
  ]
  
  DOMAINS: [economic, strategic, temporal]
  
  ACTION: synthesize
  
  OUTPUT: recommendation
}


⸻

Key Design Rules
	•	Meaning is resolved at runtime, not encoded statically
	•	Constraints are explicit and attachable
	•	Domains are selective, not exhaustive
	•	Output must include:
	•	action
	•	confidence
	•	reasoning trace (compressed)

